    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I ran into a problem with **reverseHighlighting** and **non alphanumeric characters** where I didn't find which logic to follow. I expose below the 3 method I came across so I can get your thoughts on that.\r\n\r\nCould you please let me know what you think/which way is the best for you?\r\n\r\nSorry for the low quality post\r\n\r\n1. The **actual behavior** that autocomplete follows, which leaves any non alphanumeric character **bold**.\r\n![actual_behavior](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20689156/100765056-5c18cd00-33f7-11eb-8816-336416826043.gif)\r\n\r\n2. The **sibling behavior**, where the non alphanumeric character will take the highlighted value of the **previous** and **next** element if they match, reverse it if they don't.\r\n![sibling_behavior](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20689156/100765136-72268d80-33f7-11eb-9117-dc4c57627b92.gif)\r\n\r\n3. The **highlight behavior**, where it just escape any non alphanumeric characters like the current **highlight** method.\r\n![highlight_behavior](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20689156/100765106-6935bc00-33f7-11eb-98bb-b0e87ac3de2e.gif)\r\n\r\ncc @algolia/instantsearch-for-websites ",
