    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think the sibling behaviour in that case is actually correct, since you are matching on the rest of the sentence, including that closing parenthesis. I think (Mode**lExample)** looks more \"pay attention from here onwards\", while (Mode**lExample**) looks like \"pay only attention to 'lExample'\", which will be odd if there's other highlighted text after this word.\r\n\r\nGoogle's autocomplete seems to try following a sibling behaviour, although it often sees separators as typos and won't highlight the match",
